Package: clickme
Maintainer: Nacho Caballero <nachocab@gmail.com>
Author: Nacho Caballero <nachocab@gmail.com>
Version: 0.2.0
License: GPL-3
Title: Straight from R to JS: Render JavaScript visualizations using R objects.
Description: R has powerful data processing abilities, but it can only generate
    static plots. Browsers allow interactivity but the data they use is often
    statically defined. Clickme bridges both worlds by making it easy to create
    interactive visualizations using data in R.
Imports:
    knitr,
    yaml (>= 2.1.7),
    stringr
Suggests:
    testthat,
    stringr,
    roxygen2
Collate:
    'utils.R'
    'opts.R'
    'root-path.R'
    'new-ractive.R'
    'validate-ractive.R'
    'data-names.R'
    'clickme.R'
    'clickme-package.r'
